Baby Freya was born at 10.16am, weighing 4lb 11oz.

When the couple arrived at Mr Barton’s brother’s house minutes later, local residents rushed to help.

Fortunately, a health visitor and a fireman trained in first aid were both nearby and offered assistance to the family.

An ambulance was called and the trio were taken to Furness General Hospital.

