As Freya was born two and a half weeks prematurely, Mrs Barton and her daughter stayed in hospital overnight so staff could make sure all was well.

The family left hospital on Saturday afternoon and have since found the funny side of their ordeal.

‘It’s definitely a story to tell the kids and grandchildren,’ said Mr Barton.

